s/\"Affinity allows you to create document templates, which typically contain placeholder content and have an .aftemplate file extension. Add folders to search for templates in using the + icon at the top left.\\r\\n\\r\\nDefaults, text attributes, object properties, stroke \/ fill color, ruler \/ column guides, grid setup and much more are saved in templates.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt can be useful to store templates in a shared location, so a design team can access a pool of managed documents. If the template folder also contains Affinity documents (.af) they will be treated as templates.\";/\"Affinity allows you to create document templates, which typically contain placeholder content and have an .aftemplate file extension. Add folders to search for templates in using the + icon at the top left.\\r\\n\\r\\n기본값s, text attributes, object properties, stroke \/ fill color, ruler \/ column guides, grid setup and much more are saved in templates.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt can be useful to store templates in a shared location, so a design team can access a pool of managed documents. If the template folder also contains Affinity documents (.af) they will be treated as templates.\";/
